<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP21_ProjectGold_Ballroom" s="489796">
  <T n="category">488441<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_EP21_ProjectGold--></T>
  <T n="name">0xABCF2F30<!--String: "Grand Ball"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_GrandBall1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:805cf07294f2d1c4</T>
      <T n="text">0x514D3381<!--String: "Dazzle your guests with a high-class Grand Ball!\n\nSims can now host a <b><font color='#199C2C'>Grand Ball Event</font></b> on their home lot, or other compatible venues. A <b><font color='#199C2C'>Waltzing Dance Floor (Medium or Grand)</font></b> is required, which can be acquired in Build mode.\n\nThe pinnacle of a Grand Ball event is the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Grand Waltz</font></b>, an elegantly coordinated dance between multiple Dance Partners."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_GrandBall2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:805cf07294f2d1c7</T>
      <T n="text">0x68A05F4C<!--String: "Should a Guest grab your Sim's interest, they can try and <b><font color='#199C2C'>Ask them to become Dance Partners</font></b>, which ensures they will dance as a pair during the Grand Waltz. If your Sim did not manage to find a Dance Partner for the Grand Waltz, fret not! They will be paired at random with another partnerless Guest.\n\nYou may choose to partner for <b><font color='#199C2C'>Friendship, Romance or Social Status</font></b>, but a guest may reject your Sim if the request seems inappropriate. A request for Friendship is usually more likely to succeed. It can also help if the two Sims have compatible personalities, already like each other, are of similar Noble status or are in allied Dynasties.\n\nTeen Sims may be Dance Partners with each other, but not with Adults."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP21\UI\Tutorial\EP21_Lessons_GrandBall3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:805cf07294f2d1c6</T>
      <T n="text">0x4311349E<!--String: "Now that your Sim has a Dance Partner, what's next? If you're dancing for <b><font color='#199C2C'>Romance or Status</font></b>, you can continue developing the connection with your Dance Partner by getting them in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>right mood</font></b>!\n\nA <b><font color='#199C2C'>Flirty</font></b> mood is ideal when dancing for Romance, which can be achieved through Flirty interactions. A <b><font color='#199C2C'>Confident</font></b> mood is best when dancing for Status, which can be achieved by giving Compliments. This will help ensure your chemistry for all Guests to witness during the Grand Waltz, and for them to remember you long after.\n\nIf you're worried that your Sim might be rejected by a prospective Dance Partner, don't let that stop you! There's always a chance your Sim gets lucky and dances with a high-status partner. It doesn't hurt to try!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
  <L n="tags">
    <E>Lesson_EP21_ProjectGold</E>
  </L>
